title: Meal Tracker
parent_desc: Encourage your child to create a food chart and record their daily meals for the week.
child_desc: Hi _______, please create a food chart and write down everything you eat for each meal every day. This way, you can keep track of what you are eating and learn more about your food choices. Its a great way to become more aware of your dietary habits (that is how much junk food vs healthy food you are consuming) and make healthier decisions.
purpose_outcome: This activity promotes awareness of dietary habits and encourages healthy eating practices. By documenting their meals, your child will gain insight into their food choices

title: Draw and Paint
parent_desc: Your child will make a collage using dried leaves/twigs and flowers that they collect themselves
purpose_outcome: This activity encourages exploration and enhances their creativity.

title: Newspaper Puzzle
parent_desc: Create a daily puzzle for your child by cutting a newspaper photo into 9-12 pieces for them to solve and enjoy.
purpose_outcome: Child gets habituated to go through newspaper daily Turning pages of paper improves fine motor skills

title: Jogging time
parent_desc: Go with your child for a short jog in the neighbourhood. Later ask child to draw a picture of what he/ she observed. This picture should have at least 7-8 elements that they saw
purpose_outcome: This activity enhances observation skills and encourages attention to detail.
